 MEAN Stack Deployment to Ubuntu in AWS


#What is the MEAN Stack?
  The MEAN Stack is a full-stack JavaScript solution used for building dynamic web applications.

MEAN Stack Components
 1 ...MongoDB= NoSQL database (document-oriented)
 2 ...Express.js= Backend framework for Node.js
 3  ... Angular= Frontend framework for building UI
 4  ... Node.js= Server environment for executing JavaScript


 #Deployment on an AWS Ubuntu EC2 instance involves#
Provisioning the server
Installing Node.js + npm
Installing MongoDB
Building & running Express backend
Building & running Angular frontend
Connecting Angular → Express → MongoDB
Optional: Production level setup (PM2, Nginx)


STEP 1 — Launch Ubuntu EC2 Instance
  Basic knowledge of **Linux commands**, **Node.js**, and **MongoDB**

 sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Install MongoDB
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
sudo systemctl start mongod
sudo systemctl enable mongod
sudo systemctl status mongod
step2
   Create a Folder named ‘Books’
  mkdir Books && cd Books
Run npm init -y

STEP 3 — Install Node.js 
 npm install express mongoose body-parser

 start the server
node server.js

The server is now up and running, we can connect it via port 3300.
the server runs on port 3300

Now we can access our Book Register web application from the internet with a browser using Public IP address or Public DNS name

